        <content><![CDATA[ <h1 class="title topictitle1">Discovery schedules</h1>  <div class="body conbody">  <p class="p"><span class="ph">A schedule determines what horizontal discovery searches          for, when it runs, and which MID Servers are used.</span></p>  <div class="p">Use the Discovery Schedule module in the Discovery application to:<ul class="ul" id="discovery_schedule_list-normal__d34279e892"><li class="li">Configure device identification by IP address or other identifiers.</li><li class="li">Determine if credentials are used in device probes.</li><li class="li">Name the MID Server to use for a particular type of discovery.</li><li class="li">Create or disable a schedule that controls when the discovery runs in your            network.</li><li class="li">Configure the use of multiple Shazzam probes for load balancing.</li><li class="li">Configure the use of multiple MID Servers for load balancing.</li><li class="li">Run a discovery manually.</li></ul></div> </div> <div class="related-links"><div class="relinfo"><div class="reltitle">Related information<br /><div><a class="link" href="https://docs.servicenow.com/?context&#61;CSHelp:Discovery_Schedule&amp;version&#61;kingston" target="_blank">Discovery schedules</a></div></div></div></div>]]></content>
